			<item>
				<title>The UK Will Scan Asylum-Seekers’ Faces for Age Checks—Despite Knowing the Tech Is Flawed</title>
				<link>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/the-uk-will-scan-asylum-seekers-faces-for-age-checksdespite-knowing-the-tech-is-flawed/</link>
				<pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 06:22:43 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/the-uk-will-scan-asylum-seekers-faces-for-age-checksdespite-knowing-the-tech-is-flawed/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;img class=&#34;img-fluid &#34;&#xA;            src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1593781493314-ee47b5274316-2800x1867.png&#34;&#xA;             srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1593781493314-ee47b5274316-576x384.webp 576w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1593781493314-ee47b5274316-768x512.webp 768w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1593781493314-ee47b5274316-992x661.webp 992w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1593781493314-ee47b5274316-1200x800.webp 1200w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1593781493314-ee47b5274316-1400x933.webp 1400w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1593781493314-ee47b5274316-2800x1867.webp 2800w&#34; sizes=&#34;100vw&#34; height=&#34;1867&#34; width=&#34;2800&#34; alt=&#34;Featured Image&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34; class=&#34;heading &#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;a href=&#34;#introduction&#34; aria-labelledby=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;!-- &lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; --&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;svg-inline--fa fas fa-link anchor&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; role=&#34;img&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 576 512&#34;&gt;&lt;use href=&#34;#fas-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&amp;nbsp;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The UK Home Office has been testing age-verification technology to determine the age of asylum seekers. However, internal tests have revealed that the technology is prone to life-altering errors. Despite these risks, the Home Office is moving forward with the plan to use this technology, raising concerns about the potential consequences for asylum seekers.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>Midjourney goes from generating ‘cat images’ to full-body ultrasound scans</title>
				<link>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/midjourney-goes-from-generating-cat-images-to-full-body-ultrasound-scans/</link>
				<pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 06:22:39 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/midjourney-goes-from-generating-cat-images-to-full-body-ultrasound-scans/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;img class=&#34;img-fluid &#34;&#xA;            src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/06ultrasound_phantom_segmentation-b254a71d083eb5c9-2800x1031.png&#34;&#xA;             srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/06ultrasound_phantom_segmentation-b254a71d083eb5c9-576x212.webp 576w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/06ultrasound_phantom_segmentation-b254a71d083eb5c9-768x283.webp 768w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/06ultrasound_phantom_segmentation-b254a71d083eb5c9-992x365.webp 992w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/06ultrasound_phantom_segmentation-b254a71d083eb5c9-1200x442.webp 1200w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/06ultrasound_phantom_segmentation-b254a71d083eb5c9-1400x515.webp 1400w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/06ultrasound_phantom_segmentation-b254a71d083eb5c9-2800x1031.webp 2800w&#34; sizes=&#34;100vw&#34; height=&#34;1031&#34; width=&#34;2800&#34; alt=&#34;Featured Image&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction-to-midjourneys-new-venture&#34; class=&#34;heading &#34;&gt;Introduction to Midjourney&amp;rsquo;s New Venture&lt;a href=&#34;#introduction-to-midjourneys-new-venture&#34; aria-labelledby=&#34;introduction-to-midjourneys-new-venture&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;!-- &lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; --&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;svg-inline--fa fas fa-link anchor&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; role=&#34;img&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 576 512&#34;&gt;&lt;use href=&#34;#fas-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&amp;nbsp;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Midjourney, a company known for its AI image generator that can produce stunning &amp;ldquo;cat pictures&amp;rdquo; and other artistic creations, has recently unveiled its first hardware product. The Midjourney Scanner, an ultrasound-based full-body scanner, marks a significant shift in the company&amp;rsquo;s focus from artificial intelligence to medical technology. In this article, we will delve into the details of this new product, its potential applications, and what this means for the future of Midjourney.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>Second carcass-eating fly species cleared by FDA for maggot wound therapy</title>
				<link>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/second-carcass-eating-fly-species-cleared-by-fda-for-maggot-wound-therapy/</link>
				<pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 04:41:53 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/second-carcass-eating-fly-species-cleared-by-fda-for-maggot-wound-therapy/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;img class=&#34;img-fluid &#34;&#xA;            src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/06GettyImages-829469540-1152x648-2800x1575.png&#34;&#xA;             srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/06GettyImages-829469540-1152x648-576x324.webp 576w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/06GettyImages-829469540-1152x648-768x432.webp 768w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/06GettyImages-829469540-1152x648-992x558.webp 992w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/06GettyImages-829469540-1152x648-1200x675.webp 1200w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/06GettyImages-829469540-1152x648-1400x787.webp 1400w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/06GettyImages-829469540-1152x648-2800x1575.webp 2800w&#34; sizes=&#34;100vw&#34; height=&#34;1575&#34; width=&#34;2800&#34; alt=&#34;Featured Image&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction-to-maggot-therapy&#34; class=&#34;heading &#34;&gt;Introduction to Maggot Therapy&lt;a href=&#34;#introduction-to-maggot-therapy&#34; aria-labelledby=&#34;introduction-to-maggot-therapy&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;!-- &lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; --&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;svg-inline--fa fas fa-link anchor&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; role=&#34;img&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 576 512&#34;&gt;&lt;use href=&#34;#fas-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&amp;nbsp;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Maggot therapy, also known as maggot debridement therapy (MDT), is a type of biotherapy that involves the use of live maggots to clean and heal wounds. The concept of maggot therapy has been around for centuries, with reports of its use dating back to the American Civil War. Despite its long history, maggot therapy has only recently gained popularity as a treatment option for chronic wounds, such as diabetic foot ulcers and venous leg ulcers.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>The Korean Telecom Giant at the Center of Anthropic’s Mythos Controversy</title>
				<link>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/the-korean-telecom-giant-at-the-center-of-anthropics-mythos-controversy/</link>
				<pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 04:41:36 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/the-korean-telecom-giant-at-the-center-of-anthropics-mythos-controversy/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;img class=&#34;img-fluid &#34;&#xA;            src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1637070906584-d791e62c21b8-2800x4197.png&#34;&#xA;             srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1637070906584-d791e62c21b8-576x863.webp 576w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1637070906584-d791e62c21b8-768x1151.webp 768w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1637070906584-d791e62c21b8-992x1487.webp 992w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1637070906584-d791e62c21b8-1200x1799.webp 1200w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1637070906584-d791e62c21b8-1400x2099.webp 1400w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1637070906584-d791e62c21b8-2800x4197.webp 2800w&#34; sizes=&#34;100vw&#34; height=&#34;4197&#34; width=&#34;2800&#34; alt=&#34;Featured Image&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34; class=&#34;heading &#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;a href=&#34;#introduction&#34; aria-labelledby=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;!-- &lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; --&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;svg-inline--fa fas fa-link anchor&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; role=&#34;img&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 576 512&#34;&gt;&lt;use href=&#34;#fas-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&amp;nbsp;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The world of artificial intelligence has been abuzz with the latest controversy surrounding Anthropic, a leading AI research company, and SK Telecom, a Korean telecom giant. In a shocking turn of events, the White House ordered Anthropic to revoke SK Telecom&amp;rsquo;s access to its most advanced AI model, Claude Mythos, due to alleged ties to China. This move has sent shockwaves throughout the tech industry, raising concerns about the regulation of AI and the potential risks of collaborating with companies linked to China.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>How to turn off AI in your Google Docs</title>
				<link>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/how-to-turn-off-ai-in-your-google-docs/</link>
				<pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 04:41:28 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/how-to-turn-off-ai-in-your-google-docs/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;img class=&#34;img-fluid &#34;&#xA;            src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1631551045549-9a735b8e4ea3-2800x4197.png&#34;&#xA;             srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1631551045549-9a735b8e4ea3-576x863.webp 576w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1631551045549-9a735b8e4ea3-768x1151.webp 768w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1631551045549-9a735b8e4ea3-992x1487.webp 992w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1631551045549-9a735b8e4ea3-1200x1799.webp 1200w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1631551045549-9a735b8e4ea3-1400x2099.webp 1400w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1631551045549-9a735b8e4ea3-2800x4197.webp 2800w&#34; sizes=&#34;100vw&#34; height=&#34;4197&#34; width=&#34;2800&#34; alt=&#34;Featured Image&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34; class=&#34;heading &#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;a href=&#34;#introduction&#34; aria-labelledby=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;!-- &lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; --&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;svg-inline--fa fas fa-link anchor&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; role=&#34;img&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 576 512&#34;&gt;&lt;use href=&#34;#fas-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&amp;nbsp;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Are you tired of seeing &amp;ldquo;write with Gemini&amp;rdquo; pop-ups in your Google Docs? You&amp;rsquo;re not alone. Many users have been experiencing this issue, and it can be frustrating, especially when you&amp;rsquo;re in the middle of an important project. In this article, we&amp;rsquo;ll show you how to turn off AI-powered features in Google Docs and get rid of those pesky pop-ups.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
